Mauritius’s Finance Minister Jugnauth to Hold Briefing After Resign Report

-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 
2011-07-26T09:13:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-26/mauritius-s-finance-minister-jugnauth-to-hold-briefing-after-resign-report.html
Mauritian Finance Minister Pravind Jugnauth will hold a news conference at 2 p.m. in  Port Louis ,
the capital, said Mouvement Socialiste Militant, the political
party of which he’s the leader.  Jugnauth and five other minsters from his party had
resigned from the Cabinet, Radio One reported. These include
Santi Bai Hanoomanjee, the minister of health, who was arrested
by the Indian Ocean island nation’s anti-graft agency last week
for “favoritism” in awarding a tender for a hospital.  Other ministers who left the cabinet were Tourism Minister
Nandcoomar Bodha, Showkutally Soodhun, the minister of
cooperatives, Leela Devi Dookun-Lutchoomun of Social Security
and Civil Service Minister Ashit Gungah, Radio One said.  Mauritius’s rupee strengthened less than 0.1 percent
against the dollar to 28.05 by 1:10 p.m. in Port Louis.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in Port Louis at 
 kbhuckory@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
